SIMPLE: round-up
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Round-up
<hw>Round"-up`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
of collecting or gathering together scattered cattle by riding around
them and driving them in.</def> <mark>[Western U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A rounding up, or upward curvature or convexity, as
in the deck of a vessel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A gathering in of scattered persons or things;
<as>as, a <ex>round-up</ex> of criminals</as>.</def> <mark>[Colloq., U.
S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Round up</ent>⟦br⟧
